31.07	Texas_Declaration_of_Independence	Texas Declaration of Independence	The Texas Declaration of Independence was the formal declaration of independence of the Republic of Texas from Mexico in the Texas Revolution. It was adopted at the Convention of 1836 at Washington-on-the-Brazos on March 2, 1836, and formally signed the following day after errors were noted in the text.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4d/Texas_Declaration_of_Independence.jpg/200px-Texas_Declaration_of_Independence.jpg
